				<p>jenn &#8211; for the pops, I insert the stick first and then dip the entire ball in the candy coating very carefully. Make sure chocolate surrounds the stick at the base to help secure the ball. Then gently tap off excess while you twirl the cake pop.</p>
<p>Also, I haven&#8217;t used Wilton melts, but a lot of others have and I am thinking they might be a little more difficult to work with. I need to try them out and see.</p>
<p> jaina &#8211; thanks!</p>
